-- FACTBOX: Toshiba bids for Areva unit
-- 
-- Fri Sep 4, 2009 10:11am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/09/04/us-areva-toshiba-sb-idUSTRE5833RG20090904

 

 (Reuters) - Japan's Toshiba Corp plans to bid for French nuclear group Areva's power transmission and distribution (T&D) unit, sources with knowledge of the situation said on Friday, in a deal that could top $5 billion. 

 Following are some facts about the transmission and distribution (T&D) equipment divisions of Areva and Toshiba: * AREVA: -- Designs and builds systems to manage power networks and the distribution of electricity from power stations. -- Provides substation equipment such as transformers, circuit breakers, disconnectors and instrument transformers. -- Provides consulting, asset management, refurbishment and spare-part services to manage electrical installations. -- French state has a 91 percent stake via various entities. -- Employs 30,000 people. -- T&D activities account for 38 percent of group sales. Unit had revenue of 5.1 billion euros ($7.3 billion) in 2008. * TOSHIBA: -- Provides transmission and distribution systems; control and measuring systems and equipment; industrial computers; rolling stock electrical systems; rechargeable batteries; solar photovoltaic systems. -- Key products include gas insulated switchgear, surge arresters, network control systems, protection & control systems, insular products, power electronics systems, transformers, switchgears, power supply systems and full turnkey project engineering. -- T & D is part of the social infrastructure segment of Toshiba, which employs 74,000 people and had 2,419 billion yen in sales in 2008, 29 percent of the group's total. (Writing by Carl Bagh, Bangalore Editorial Reference Unit; Editing by  David Cutler  and  David Holmes ) ($1=.7008 Euro)